# Floor for the deployed quiz game. This is the oldest environment we still
# want first-class support for after the bundle-size audit: a Xiaomi Mi Note 3
# running Android 9 reports Chrome 138, but the device is constrained enough
# that we should not assume anything beyond ES2019 + HTTP fetch baseline.
#
# Modern Chrome (>= 90) covers everything below ES2020, so `defaults` alone is
# too generous — it ships ES2022+ regex / class fields. We deliberately do NOT
# include `last 2 versions` so that a contributor bumping Vite's default
# `build.target` does not silently start emitting syntax older Chrome cannot
# parse on Android 9 WebView-derived runtimes.
last 2 Chrome versions
last 2 Safari versions
last 2 Samsung versions
Android >= 9
not dead
